  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "8. Solomon kept the feast seven days—The time chosen for the dedication of the temple was immediately previous to the feast of tabernacles (see on [423]1Ki 8:1-12). That season, which came after the harvest, corresponding to our September and October, lasted seven days, and during so prolonged a festival there was time afforded for the offering of the immense sacrifices enumerated. A large proportion of these were peace offerings, which afforded to the people the means of festive enjoyment.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "all Israel … from the entering in of Hamath—that is, the defile at Lebanon.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "unto the river of Egypt—that is, Rhinocorura, now El-Arish, the south boundary of Palestine.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
